Class AtomDictionary

  • java.lang.Object
    • models.Atom<java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,Atom<?>>>
      • models.AtomDictionary

  • public class AtomDictionary
extends Atom<java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,Atom<?>>>
    A dictionary is encoded as de. The elements of the dictionary are encoded each key immediately followed by its value. All keys must be byte strings and must appear in lexicographical order. A dictionary that associates the values 42 and "spam" with the keys "foo" and "bar", respectively (in other words, {"bar": "spam", "foo": 42}}), would be encoded as follows: d3:bar4:spam3:fooi42ee. (This might be easier to read by inserting some spaces: d 3:bar 4:spam 3:foo i42e e.)
    Author:
    Graham Fairweather
    See Also:
    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bencode}
